  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "SUPERVISOR",
  "description": "<h3>Job Description:</h3>\n<p>Schedules, assigns and plans the work of carpentry factory personnel performing a variety of carpentry projects.</p>\n<p>Plans and develops work schedules, equipment usage schedules, priority of carpentry expenditures and procedures for equipment maintenance.</p>\n<p>Supervises carpenters to ensure safety and quality in the performance of assigned tasks.</p>\n<p>Take measurements and calculate the size and amount of material needed.</p>\n<p>Constructs custom cabinetry and furniture as needed; repairs or modifies furniture as needed.</p>\n<p>Conform to an established work schedule.</p>\n<p>Reading blueprints, drawings and sketches to fully grasp requirements</p>\n<h3>Requirements:</h3>\n<p>Minimum 3 years related experience</p>\n<p>Good interpersonal communication and problem solving skills</p>\n<p>Good management of materials cost and stock inventory</p>\n<p>Experience of using hand and power tools such as drills, chisels, sanders, saws and nail guns</p>\n<p>Joinery and cabinet making skills</p>\n<p>Able to work for long hours period or night shift</p>\n<p>Able to work on weekends and public holidays</p>\n<p>have driving license</p>",
